article.headline: Texas A&M-Corpus Christi 85, Cent. Arkansas 73
article.story: CONWAY, Ark. (AP) -- Texas A&M-Corpus Christi's Chris Daniels made 75 percent of his field-goal attempts Saturday night and finished with 34 points to lead the Islanders to an 85-73 Southland Conference victory over Central Arkansas. A&M-Corpus Christi (12-4, 3-0 SLC) trailed 33-32 at the half, but boosted the accuracy of its shooting significantly after intermission to get the win. In the first half, there was little difference between the shooting accuracy of UCA (6-11, 1-3), at 46 percent, and that of the visitors, who shot 45 percent. But in the second period, the Islanders hit a blazing 67 percent of their shots from the field. UCA boosted its accuracy, too, but only to 52 percent. Scooby Johnson added 13 points for A&M-Corpus Christi, with Taurean Mitchell scoring 12. Marcus Pillow led the Bears' offense, with 24 points, including 4-of-8 shooting from 3-point range. Durrell Nevels scored 12 points for UCA.
